<section class="page-hero about-hero"><p class="eyebrow">About Nirog Bhumi</p><h1>Understand who we are.</h1></section>
<section class="accordion-section"><details open><summary>1. What is Nirog Bhumi?</summary><p>Nirog Bhumi is a science-backed, nature-rooted diabetes reversal platform. We help people with Type 2 diabetes, prediabetes and insulin resistance work toward diabetes reversal and better metabolic health through structured lifestyle transformation.</p><p>Our work brings together food regulation, yoga, naturopathy, Ayurveda, acupressure, meditation, breathwork, sleep correction, habit tracking and community support. The goal is not just to lower blood sugar numbers temporarily, but to improve the internal conditions that shape blood sugar in the first place.</p><p>Nirog Bhumi exists to make diabetes reversal understandable, practical, measurable and sustainable. “Nirog” means free from disease and “Bhumi” means earth, ground or foundation. Together, Nirog Bhumi means a healing ground and expresses our larger dream of an earth free from disease.</p></details><details ><summary>2. Why do we exist?</summary><p>For years, many people have been told that Type 2 diabetes is a lifelong condition that can only be managed. We believe this story is incomplete.</p><p>Modern research now recognises that Type 2 diabetes can go into remission in many people when the body’s metabolic environment changes deeply enough. This does not mean making casual promises of a cure. It means working seriously and responsibly toward restoring glucose regulation through a structured lifestyle system.</p><p>Nirog Bhumi exists for people who want to undertake this journey toward good metabolic health and freedom, with guidance, discipline and support.</p></details><details ><summary>3. What is our approach towards diabetes reversal?</summary><p>Our approach is to work on the root causes of diabetes. Blood sugar is the visible number, but Type 2 diabetes is shaped by much more happening in the background: insulin resistance, excess fat in the liver and pancreas, chronic inflammation, poor sleep, stress, sedentary living, processed foods, weak digestion and a disturbed metabolic environment.</p><p>At Nirog Bhumi, we focus on improving these underlying conditions through food, movement, sleep, stress regulation, digestion, connection with nature and daily discipline. When the body’s metabolic environment begins to heal, blood sugar regulation can improve and the body can move naturally toward diabetes reversal.</p></details><details ><summary>4. How do we combine science and nature?</summary><p>We combine modern diabetes remission research with traditional Indian healing systems. Science helps us understand insulin resistance, ectopic fat, beta-cell stress, inflammation, glucose uptake, hunger hormones, stress pathways and metabolic recovery.</p><p>Nature gives us practical tools: plant-based whole foods, yoga, naturopathy, Ayurveda, acupressure, pranayama, meditation, sunlight, sleep rhythm and disciplined living. We do not use these practices as wellness decoration; we use them as biological tools.</p><p>Movement supports glucose uptake, food regulation reduces metabolic load, yoga supports core strength and insulin sensitivity, pranayama calms the nervous system, meditation builds awareness and discipline, and sleep supports hormonal balance. This is how Nirog Bhumi connects ancient wisdom with modern metabolic science.</p></details><details ><summary>5. What does remission mean to us?</summary><p>To us, remission means moving Type 2 diabetes below the diabetic range in a measurable and medically responsible way. The American Diabetes Association-led international consensus report proposed remission as the appropriate term and defined the usual diagnostic criterion as HbA1c below 6.5%, measured at least three months after stopping glucose-lowering medication.</p><p>HbA1c of 6.5% is the diagnostic threshold for diabetes. When HbA1c remains below this level without diabetes medication, the body is no longer showing diabetes-range blood sugar at that point in time.</p><p>Remission is not the same as a permanent cure. It must be protected through continued lifestyle discipline, regular monitoring and responsible medical guidance. At Nirog Bhumi, remission is not treated as a one-time event; it is the result of a new way of living.</p></details></section>
